## 🧠 Memory System Integration (MemoryHub)

### Auto-Sync Architecture
The MemoryHub system runs as a background daemon that:
1. Scans session JSONL files every 5 minutes for new content
2. Extracts meaningful user↔agent exchanges
3. Generates structured summaries
4. Embeds and stores in vector database
5. Provides semantic search via MCP tools

### Available MCP Tools
- `mem_save` — Save a memory to vector store
- `mem_search` — Semantic search across all memories
- `mem_stats` — View memory statistics
- `mem_list_collections` — List all memory collections
- `mem_delete` — Remove a memory entry

### When to Use Memory Tools
| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| User asks "what did we do before..." | `mem_search` |
| Completing important task | `mem_save` |
| Found a bug/fix | `mem_save` with tags=["踩坑"] |
| User corrected you | `mem_save` with tags=["修正"] |
| Starting new project phase | `mem_search` for context |
| End of work session | `mem_save` summary + update daily log |

### Memory Files (always kept in sync)
```
workspace/
├── MEMORY.md              # Long-term memory
├── memory/
│   ├── daily/             # Daily work logs
│   ├── projects/          # Project-specific memory
│   └── lessons/           # Mistakes and learnings
└── .learnings/            # Self-improvement logs
```

### Daemon Health Check
```bash
# Check if MemoryHub scanner is running
pgrep -f "session_scanner.py"

# Check vector store
curl -s http://localhost:6333/health

# View recent scans
cat ~/.memory-hub/scan_state.json
```
